<h1>602+ agencies have access to South Portland's Flock cameras</h1>

<p>The FOAA-obtained <code>SharedNetworks_2026_May_5.csv</code> lists every agency that SPPD shares Flock data with. After normalizing organization names and filtering to rows where SPPD is actively sharing data (<code>Networks I'm Sharing</code> is non-null), the dataset contains <strong>{{ agencies.length }} agencies</strong>.</p>

<h2>Verify this yourself</h2>

<h3>Step 1: Download the data</h3>

<p><a href="{{ "/data/derived/sppd-shared-networks/sppd-shared-networks-normalized.csv" | url }}" class="cta">Download sppd-shared-networks-normalized.csv</a></p>

<p>Or download the raw source from the repo:</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="{{ "/data/sppd-foaa-2026-audit-logs/raw-monthly/SharedNetworks_2026_May_5.csv" | url }}">SharedNetworks_2026_May_5.csv</a> (raw Flock spreadsheet)</li>
  <li><a href="{{ "/data/derived/sppd-shared-networks/sppd-shared-networks-normalized.csv" | url }}">sppd-shared-networks-normalized.csv</a> (normalized output)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Step 2: Open in a spreadsheet</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Open Google Sheets or Excel</li>
  <li>Go to <strong>File → Import → Upload</strong></li>
  <li>Upload <code>sppd-shared-networks-normalized.csv</code></li>
  <li>Select comma as delimiter; the file has headers in row 1</li>
</ol>

<h3>Step 3: Count the agencies</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Select the entire column A (<code>normalized_org_name</code>)</li>
  <li>In a blank cell, enter: <code>=COUNTA(A2:A)</code> (Google Sheets) or <code>=COUNTA(A:A)-1</code> (Excel)</li>
  <li>The result should be <strong>{{ agencies.length }}</strong></li>
</ol>

<h3>Step 4: Verify the filter</h3>

<p>The 602 count includes only agencies where SPPD <em>actively shares</em> data. To verify the filter:</p>
<ol>
  <li>In the raw <code>SharedNetworks_2026_May_5.csv</code>, filter column C (<code>Networks I'm Sharing</code>) to non-blank values</li>
  <li>Count the remaining rows — this is the pre-normalization number of sharing agencies</li>
  <li>After normalization (stripping vendor suffixes like "Flex", "LR"), duplicates are merged, producing the final {{ agencies.length }} count</li>
</ol>

<h2>Sample agencies</h2>

